  "examTip": "NAT translates private IP addresses (RFC 1918: 10.x.x.x, 172.16.x.x, 192.168.x.x) to a single public IP address. The NAT router maintains a translation table that maps {Private IP : Private Port} ↔ {Public IP : Public Port}. NAPT/PAT uses different port numbers to distinguish connections from multiple internal hosts sharing the same public IP. Return packets are matched against the table using destination IP:port and translated back to the internal host.",
